  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Fire Protection Engineer",
  "description": "<h3>Fire Protection Engineer</h3>\n<h3>Visit www.ourrecruiters.com</h3>\n<p><strong>Duties &amp; Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Monitor and supervise subcontractors' work according to shop drawings, method statements, materials, and samples.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with authorities, subcontractors, or clients on shop drawings, materials, and samples.</li>\n  <li>Review fire protection design drawings for compliance with specifications (Sprinkler System, Fire Alarm System, Hosereel System, Wet/Dry Riser System, Fire Hydrant System, Fireman Intercom System).</li>\n  <li>Identify discrepancies between M&amp;E, structural, ID, architectural, and client provisions.</li>\n  <li>Manage and execute projects according to schedule.</li>\n  <li>Attend meetings with contractors to address issues and update progress.</li>\n  <li>Review drawings and specifications for compliance.</li>\n  <li>Allocate work to supervisors, ensuring standards and SOP compliance.</li>\n  <li>Plan and lead testing and commissioning of fire protection systems.</li>\n  <li>Follow up on inspections, defect rectifications, and maintenance during DLP.</li>\n  <li>Plan and prepare OMM, training, and as-built drawings for handover.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Education/Experience/Special Skills</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Mechanical Engineering/Building Services or Diploma in Mechanical Engineering/Building Services.</li>\n  <li>5 years of relevant experience.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in MS Office.</li>\n  <li>Good communication and writing skills.</li>\n  <li>Experience in Water Mist or foam systems is an advantage.</li>\n  <li>Independent worker with good interpersonal skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Work Areas</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Positions for 1 senior and 1 junior at Changi site.</li>\n</ul>",
